vulnerability.name: USN-7443-1
vulnerability.description: Fabian Bäumer, Marcel Maehren, Marcus Brinkmann, and Jörg Schwenk discovered that Erlang OTP’s SSH module incorrect handled authentication. A remote attacker could use this issue to execute arbitrary commands without authentication, possibly leading to a system compromise.

statements.status_notes: Erlang could be made to run programs if it received specially crafted network traffic.
